"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-10-05-date-a421-reopen-revealed-29-olympic-pools-water-removed-21739776\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tbrowser thatsupports HTML5 \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tvideo  Up Next  A major road submerged by floodwater could reopen as early as next week after a month ofrainfell in less than two days.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 43, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5104783076127343e-14, \"text\": \"JavaScript\", \"types\": [\"Q9143\", \"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\"}, {\"begin\": 105, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"score\": 0.9999999999654392, \"rank\": 3.458882471519876e-11, \"text\": \"HTML5\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The boot of a car was pictured poking out of the 8ft deep water along the A421 inBedfordshire, where a roadside pumping station has reappeared after two weeks.\", \"from\": 256, \"to\": 415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It simply got totally overwhelmed by the sheer volume of water that fell here in such a short space of time', said Martin Fellows, theNational Highwaysregional director.\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 587, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 533, \"end\": 539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"score\": 0.8199292746097799, \"rank\": 0.21961738660298671, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The road has been closed in both directions, between the A6 at Bedford to the M1 junction 13 near Brogborough/Marston Moretaine, since the 'one in 100 year event' on September 22.\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 652, \"end\": 659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bedford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7427685479318693e-18, \"text\": \"Bedford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bedford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bedford\"}, {\"begin\": 687, \"end\": 698, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brogborough\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brogborough\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brogborough\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brogborough\"}, {\"begin\": 699, \"end\": 716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marston_Moreteyne\", \"score\": 0.9999999999913598, \"rank\": 8.774584278425937e-12, \"text\": \"Marston Moretaine\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marston_Moreteyne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marston_Moreteyne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 72 million litres of water have already been removed through 2.5 miles of pipe and 25 tankers to balancing ponds, according to Fellows.\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Start your day informed with Metro'sNews Updatesnewsletter or getBreaking Newsalerts the moment it happens.\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the equivalent of nearly 29 Olympic swimming pools, or more than three times the length of the pitch at Wembley.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1137, \"end\": 1144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wembley\", \"score\": 0.976099936795303, \"rank\": 0.016210614968732225, \"text\": \"Wembley\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wembley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wembley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It could mean part of the road will reopen next week as early as Wednesday when the rest of the water has been removed,BBC Newsreported.\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But major repairs could be required, with at least one slip road needing to be resurfaced, further delaying its reopening,Bedford Independentreported.\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Fellows said: 'We will be working around the clock to carry out repairs and get the road reopened as soon as it is safe to do so.\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It may be possible to open some elements of the road towards the end of next week - such as one lane in each direction - but we will only do that when we are certain it's safe.'\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is anger that this happened in the first place, after the pumping station tasked with removing floodwater was itself flooded.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1882, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sue Clark, a Conservative on Central Bedfordshire Council, said: 'Nobody can think of it as anything other than a national disgrace.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 2016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1884, \"end\": 1887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\", \"score\": 0.8921162232117812, \"rank\": 0.11746483047850807, \"text\": \"Sue\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Sylvester\"}, {\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Bedfordshire_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Central Bedfordshire Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Bedfordshire_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Central_Bedfordshire_Council\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'The only way they can extract the water is by tanker, they are using a fleet of tankers and they are transporting the water into other balancing ponds or other streams that are not at capacity.'\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mohammad Yasin, the Labour MP for Bedford and Kempston, said he has been assured by Mr Fellows that the failed pumping station will be replaced.\", \"from\": 2215, \"to\": 2359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohammad_Yasin_(politician)\", \"score\": 0.9999988669207649, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mohammad Yasin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohammad_Yasin_(politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mohammad_Yasin_(politician)\"}, {\"begin\": 2235, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 0.5733107436307843, \"rank\": 0.7010136980345105, \"text\": \"Labour\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 2249, \"end\": 2256, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bedford\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7427685479318693e-18, \"text\": \"Bedford\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bedford\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bedford\"}, {\"begin\": 2261, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kempston\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.10581534781926e-29, \"text\": \"Kempston\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kempston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kempston\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blake Stephenson, the Conservative MP for Mid Bedfordshire, said: 'It beggars belief that this infrastructure was built in the way it was.'\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2361, \"end\": 2366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\", \"score\": 0.8354932207470465, \"rank\": 0.19689780060766307, \"text\": \"Blake\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\"}, {\"begin\": 2367, \"end\": 2377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Stephenson\", \"score\": 0.9976127923188255, \"rank\": 0.0023925693802359757, \"text\": \"Stephenson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Stephenson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/George_Stephenson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Fellows said: 'We will work with all the partners to ensure we can mitigate the impact and make sure it does not have such an impact again.'\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2645, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He added: 'Let us do our job, let us work and get this water cleared and get the road open as quickly and safely as possible.'\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get in touch with our news team by emailing us atwebnews@metro.co.uk.\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2832, \"end\": 2843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9993608704168107, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"metro.co.uk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our news page.\", \"from\": 2846, \"to\": 2893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:These are the best places to see the Northern Lights in the UK tonight  ArrowMORE:Major UK motorway closed in both directions following crash  ArrowMORE:How huge advertising boards made 'London's worst station' even worse  Stay on top of the hea